Number of Ukrainian recruits preparing to be sent to Donbass
The official representative of the People’s Militia of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People’s Republic (LPR) Andrei Marocko said that in the winter of 2018-2019 Ukraine will send to Donbass at least 3 thousand recruits.
According to him, in this way, Kiev plans "at least somehow to supplement the units".
“The unwillingness of Ukrainian citizens to serve in the ranks of the Ukrainian Armed Forces, mass dismissals have led to low units,” Marocko told RIA Novosti.
He also noted that the real numbers of Ukrainians called in the army could be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev launched the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by Operation Joint Forces (OAS).
It was assumed that this measure would strengthen the role of Ukrainian security forces in the settlement of the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in the Donbass worsened due to the murder of the head of the DPR Alexander Zakharchenko.
The DPR authorities qualified the incident as a terrorist attack.
During the investigation of the criminal case several people involved in the explosion were detained.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the sabotage was organized by Ukrainian special services.
US forces Musk to resign as chairman of Tesla
The American businessman Elon Musk will leave the position of chairman of the board of directors of the company he founded Tesla at the request of the U.S. authorities.
To settle claims of the Federal Securities and Exchange Commission, the entrepreneur will also pay $20 million.
According to CNBC, the pre-trial agreement with the department allows Musk to remain in the leadership position in Tesla.
At the same time, he is obliged to pay $20 million and leave the position of chairman of the board of directors within 45 days from the date of the agreement and for at least three years.
Two independent directors will be appointed in his place.
It is specified that the agreement still needs to be approved by the court.
On September 28, it became known that the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission accused Musk of misleading shareholders by stating that there were sufficient funds to buy the shares of this company and filed a lawsuit against the entrepreneur.
It is about the businessman's post on Twitter, where he said he wanted to buy back Tesla shares at $420 per piece, but never did.
After the tweet, the company’s shares rose by almost 11%.
British Foreign Minister compares EU to Soviet Union and prison
British Foreign Minister Jeremy Hunt compared the European Union to the Soviet Union and accused Brussels of capturing member states.
The statement was made at the Congress of the ruling Conservative Party in Birmingham, which opened on Sunday, September 30.
As the Daily Mail notes, Hunt commented on the difficulties in the Brexit negotiation process.
What happened to the belief in the European dream and its ideals?
The EU was created to defend freedom, and the Soviet Union did not let anyone leave it.
"The lesson of history is obvious: if you turn the EU from a community to a prison, the desire to leave it will not decrease, but will only grow, and we will not be the only prisoner who will want to escape from captivity," he said.
He also added that attempts to punish Britain for the decision to leave the European Union will only aggravate the crisis.
In mid-September, British Prime Minister Theresa May said Brexit negotiations had come to an impasse.
This was stated at the informal EU summit in Salzburg.
The decision on Brexit was made in 2016 by a referendum.
The UK’s withdrawal is expected to take place by April 2019, but negotiations with Brussels on this issue are complicated by a number of factors.
In particular, there is still no clear agreement on how the parties will interact after London leaves the community.
The issue of the Irish border remains open.
