More than 100 prisoners escaped after earthquake in Indonesia
More than 100 prisoners have escaped from a prison in the Indonesian province of Central Sulawesi.
Escape was possible after two powerful earthquakes on the island of magnitude 7.2 and 7.4.
According to The Jakarta Post, the incident occurred on September 28 when prisoners in the city of Palu demanded their release in connection with the underground raids.
More than 340 prisoners organized a riot and set fire to the institution.
The police who arrived at the scene partially took control of the situation, but more than 100 people escaped from the prison.
