The investigation was initiated against Magomed Mahatchev, other heads and employees of the territorial offices of medical and social expertise under his supervision under Article 210 (creation of a criminal community using official position and participation in it), Article 290 (receiving bribery by an organized group), Article 292 (service counterfeiting) and Article 159 (fraud in a large amount) of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
As follows from the investigation materials, at the end of 2013, Rajab Abdulatipov, aware of the illegal actions of Magomed Mahatchev and his accomplices involved in the theft of funds of the Pension Fund, joined their activities by joining a criminal community.
Being in the position of head of the Federal Migration Service of Russia for Daghestan and having links in state authorities and law enforcement structures, as well as enjoying his related relations with the head of Daghestan, Rajab Abdulatipov, the investigators believe, "provided the activities of other participants of the criminal community, established contacts with officials of state bodies to support the illegal activity of Mohammad Mahatchev and his position as head of the federal treasury institution "The Main Bureau of medical and social expertise for the Republic of Daghestan", organized the illegal establishment of disabilities to citizens".
Following the announcement of this information at the meeting of the Soviet District Court on Friday, Rajab Abdulatipov rejected the charges he was charged with.
"Of course, everything that is presented to me today as an accusation, for me all this is new, absolutely I am not familiar with it," he said.
The court arrested the deputy from "United Russia" not ten days before the indictment, as it was with previous high-ranking Dagestan officials, but immediately for two months, because in his case appears article 210 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
