The scientist told about the possible scientific program of the Russian expedition to the moon
The head of the Institute of Space Studies of the Russian Academy of Sciences, member-correspondent of the Russian Academy of Sciences Anatoly Petrukovich told RIA Novosti about a possible program of scientific research for Russian astronauts on the moon.
According to him, the scientific community is currently developing directions of such work.
"There is no consolidated opinion yet," the scientist stressed.
He noted that one option is to place a low-frequency radio telescope on the back of the moon, which would avoid interference, the source of which is the Earth.
