Names of winners of the Fazil Iskander Prize
The prize was awarded to the laureates of the Fazil Iskander Prize.
The ceremony was held at the Central House of Literatures in Moscow.
In the nomination "Prosa" the winner was Kant Ibrahimov, the novel "Stigal".
The novel "Stigal" begins as a diary of a cancer patient and turns to the end in an epic work.
In the nomination "Poetry" - Vyacheslav Shapovalov, the book of poems "Eurasian".
"Best Film Screenplay" is the work of Sergey Dmitrenko based on stories told by Fazil Iskander in the book "Sandro from Chegem".
In the nomination "Chegemsky Heights" - Auren Habichev, the series of stories "My Great Nothing".
In addition to the main contest, special diplomas were awarded to Elena Nesterina for the story "Eternal Happiness!" and Ludmila Vyazmitina for the book of poems "Mesiaceslov".
Fazil Iskander (1929 – 2016) was born in Sukhum.
In 1954 graduated from the Literary Institute.
The first poetry collections – “Mountain trails” (1957), “The Goodness of the Land” (1959), “Green Rain” (1960) – received recognition from critics and readers.
He was best known for his novel “The Constellation of Kozlotur” (1966).
His most famous novel is Sandro of Chegem.
