The Ministry of Finance forecasts a weakening of the exchange rate to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035.
The Ministry of Finance of Russia forecasts a gradual weakening of the ruble to 73.9 rubles per U.S. dollar in the period until 2036.
The ministry also forecasts the stabilization of world oil prices in the range of $40-50 per barrel during this period.
This is stated in the "Budget forecast of the Russian Federation until 2036" on the portal of the budget system.
According to the forecast of the Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation, the rate of the ruble to the U.S. dollar in the period 2021-2025 will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles per dollar, and in the period 2031-2035 - 73.9 rubles per dollar.
In addition, according to the Russian ministry, with a high probability, oil prices on the medium and long-term horizon will stabilize in the range of $ 40-45 per barrel at constant prices.
Oil of the Urals brand, according to the forecasts of the Ministry of Finance, will cost in the period 2021-2025 - $55.2 per barrel, in 2026-2030 - $52.2 per barrel, and in the period 2031-2035 - $54.9 per barrel.
