Sirius educators discussed with scientists nature-like technologies
Educators of the educational center "Sirius" in Sochi, participants of the School of Agrobiology and Plant Genetics, attended a lecture by scientists of the national research center "Kurchatov Institute".
The researchers’ speech was held within the framework of the program of the Global International Forum of Convergence and Nature-Like Technologies, organized in Sochi on behalf of Russian President Vladimir Putin, according to the website of the educational center on September 29.
The lecture was opened by the documentary film “Kurchatov’s Codes”, during which the President of the Kurchatov Institute, member-correspondent of the Russian Academy of Sciences Mikhail Kovalchuk spoke about global challenges as the driving force of civilization development.
The lecture of the scientist is published on the site "Sirius".
Students learned that modern technology requires huge amounts of energy.
Alternative energy is not yet capable of producing such amounts.
To solve this problem, according to the organizers of the forum, will help nature-like technologies, which today young scientists are working on.
In addition, Kovalchuk raised the topic of responsibility for the development of nature-like technologies, and also talked about the risks that inevitably arise when creating such technologies.
"The arrival of such technologies is a unique thing, it is a colossal good.
This is the explosive growth of medical technology, it is the improvement of quality of life and infrastructure.
But there is also the second side.
The development of nature-like technologies is actually the technological reproduction of living nature systems.
There is a reverse side - a targeted intervention in human life.
There is always risk.
A car appeared - people began to die under the wheels.
The cars are still used.
The dual nature of technology.
I’m creating medical new technology, and at the same time I can create weapons of mass destruction,” the scientist said.
After watching the film and discussing modern scientific breakthroughs, students were able to ask questions to the participants of the meeting.
In the role of speakers, the candidate of physical and mathematical sciences, the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBIX-natural-like technologies of the NIC "Kurchatov Institute" Yulia Djakov and the head of the Kurchatov complex of NBIX-technologies Vyacheslav Demin.
The “Sirius” educational center in Sochi was created by the “Talent and Success” educational foundation on the basis of the Olympic infrastructure at the initiative of Russian President Vladimir Putin.
The aim of the educational center is the early identification, development and further professional support of gifted children.
Earlier in September it was that the prize-winners of the All-Russian online Olympiad on information security "Cybervisov" will be sent to training in "Sirius".
