Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor
Residents of the Republic are increasingly visiting the official website of the Office of the Federal Service of the Judiciary of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to experts of the department of organizational and control work, informatization and information security of the republican department, over 140 thousand visits to the site, more than 42 thousand visits to the section "Bank of data of executive proceedings", 661 payment receipts for payment of debts were downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council of the Russian Federation for the Republic of Kazakhstan, virtually every resident of the region has debts for utilities payments, GIBDD fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured from unforeseen situations.
But the debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on traveling abroad.
This is why the Russian Federal Reserve for Foreign Affairs recommends that all those who have planned a trip abroad clarify in the court office at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them.
The service created the "Bank of data of executive proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communications devices iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The database contains information about the executive proceedings initiated by the Kalmytsia statues against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSP of Russia for the Republic of Kazakhstan Delgir Bodgaeva.
In the presence of debts, the system discloses information about the number and date of initiation of the executive proceedings; the name of the body that issued the executive sheet or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the department of judicial offices; the registration office of the court officer-executor; the contact phone.
Information about the course of the executive proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at the address: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
